      "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/23/2/93/1",
      "text": [
        ": الصَّلَوَاتُ الْمَفْرُوضَاتُ فِی أَوَّلِ وَقْتِهَا إِذَا أُقِیمَ حُدُودُهَا أَطْیَبُ رِیحاً مِنْ قَضِیبِ الْآسِ حِینَ یُؤْخَذُ مِنْ شَجَرِهِ فِی طِیبِهِ وَ رِیحِهِ وَ طَرَاوَتِهِ فَعَلَیْکُمْ بِالْوَقْتِ الْأَوَّلِ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.sayed-athar-husain-rizvi-&-sayed-maqsood-athar": [
          "1. Abi (rah) from Sa’d b. Abdillah from Ahmad b. Muhammad from al-Hassan b. Mahbub from Sa’d b. Abi Khalaf from Abi al-Hassan Musa (a.s.) who said: “If an obligatory prayer is offered in prime time fulfilling all the conditions a sweet smell would come out from it just like the sweet smell that comes out when a branch of tree is broken. Hence it is obligatory on you to offer Salaat at its prime time.”"
        ]
      }
    },
